      In 1984, <em>37%</em> of all students graduating with degrees in computer
      and information sciences were women. However, they comprised of
      <em>less than half</em> of that by 2010, as the industry was more willing
      to hire men.
      <hr>
      <a class="cs" href="https://www.britannica.com/science/computer-science" target="_blank">
       <em><strong>Computer science</strong></em> </a>
      is the study of how computers work, which includes software, hardware, and
      algorithms. It is the greatest tool that will help us uncover solutions to
      many of the world's challenging problems. Learning computer
      science can lead to a career in software development, game development,
      cybersecurity, artificial intelligence, web and app development, and so
      much more. All it takes is a great idea combined with coding knowledge to
      positively change the world!
